&lt;p>&lt;strong>The Container Pattern&lt;/strong>&lt;br>
&lt;span class="txt">
Each &lt;code>.tab_container&lt;/code> works as an independent component that encapsulates all its functionality – similar to how components work in modern frameworks like React or Vue.
&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Navigation and Content Pairing&lt;/strong>&lt;br>
&lt;span class="txt">
The &lt;code>.tit_list&lt;/code> element serves as the navigation menu, with each anchor element pointing to its corresponding content block via the href attribute – creating a clear relationship between tabs and content.
&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Content Containers&lt;/strong>&lt;br>
&lt;span class="txt">
Each content panel uses the &lt;code>.tab_content&lt;/code> class and has a unique ID that matches its navigation control. This relationship is what powers our tab switching mechanism.
&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
